sentences: Shoshana Rudiakov (1948–2012) was a Latvian pianist and music educator.
She was professor of piano at the State University of Music and Performing Arts Stuttgart from 1981.
Shoshana Rudiakov was born on 25 June 1948 in Riga, Latvia (then within the USSR).
She died on 21 November 2012 in Stuttgart.
After moving to Israel in 1973 she was engaged as soloist with major orchestras including the Israel Philharmonic.
Her first appearance in Western Europe was in 1975 at the Royal Albert Hall in London with the New Philharmonia Orchestra.
She moved to Germany in 1977, and performed as soloist with the Berliner Philharmoniker, Württemberg Chamber Orchestra, and Nürnberg Philharmoniker.
She was appointed professor of piano at the State University of Music and Performing Arts Stuttgart in 1981, and vice-rector in 2002.
